╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 4.2: Word and Paragraph Objects       ║
║  Category: Text Objects          Difficulty: ★★☆ Intermediate   ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  m i w   Select INSIDE word (the word itself, no surrounding space)
  m a w   Select AROUND word (includes trailing/leading whitespace)
  m i p   Select INSIDE paragraph (lines of text, no surrounding blanks)
  m a p   Select AROUND paragraph (includes surrounding blank lines)

MNEMONIC: w = word, p = paragraph

"Inside word" selects just the word characters.
"Around word" includes adjacent whitespace — useful for cleanly
removing a word without leaving double spaces.

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  Part 1: In the first paragraph, change "terrible" to "excellent"
          and "failures" to "successes" using m i w then c.

  Part 2: Delete the entire second paragraph using m a p then d.
          (Place cursor anywhere in the second paragraph first.)

  Part 3: The third paragraph should remain untouched.

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

The project had a terrible start, but the team turned their early
failures into learning opportunities. By the end of the quarter,
everyone agreed the results were remarkable.

This paragraph is temporary scaffolding that was left in the draft
by mistake. It contains nothing useful and should be removed
entirely before the document is finalized.

Ship the final version to the client by Friday. Make sure to
include the executive summary and the quarterly projections
in the appendix.

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

The project had a excellent start, but the team turned their early
successes into learning opportunities. By the end of the quarter,
everyone agreed the results were remarkable.

Ship the final version to the client by Friday. Make sure to
include the executive summary and the quarterly projections
in the appendix.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Move to "terrible", press m i w to select just that word,
          then c to change it. Type "excellent" and press Esc.
  Hint 2: Move to "failures", press m i w then c, type "successes".
  Hint 3: For the second paragraph, place cursor on any word in it,
          press m a p to select the whole paragraph including the
          blank lines around it, then d to delete.
  Hint 4: Using m a p (around) instead of m i p (inside) ensures
          the blank lines are also removed, avoiding extra gaps.
